<div id="wb_element_instance845" class="wb_element" style=" line-height: normal;"><h3 class="wb-stl-heading3" style="text-align: center;"><span style="color:#inherit;"><strong>ARGENTINA LUXURY</strong></span></h3>

<p><br>
 </p>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;">YOU WILL KNOW THE CITY OF TANGO IN ITS ENTIRE SPLENDOR, ONE OF THE MOST BEAUTIFUL NATURAL WONDERS OF LATIN AMERICA AS IGUAZU FALLS, WILL FREEZE TO CONTEMPLATE THE STUNNING PERITO MORENO GLACIER AND ENJOY THE TIERRA DEL FUEGO NATIONAL PARK, THE SOUTHERNMOST OF THE WORLD. ALL THIS AND MORE IN 15 DAYS OF PASSAGE.</h1>

<p><strong><span style="color: rgb(12, 46, 6); font-family: Batang, serif; font-size: 20px; text-align: justify; text-transform: uppercase; background-color: transparent;"> </span></strong></p>

<h3 class="wb-stl-heading3" style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">ARGENTINA LUXURY: </span></strong><strong style="background-color: transparent;"><span style="background-color: transparent;">Ciudad de Buenos Aires | Iguazú | Ushuaia | El Calafate</span></strong></h3>

<h3 class="wb-stl-heading3" style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">15 DAYS / 13 NIGHTS</span></strong></h3>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;"> </span></strong></h1>

<p> </p>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">The program includes the following services:</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">* Transfers Airport/ Hotel/ Airport<br>
* 4 nights lodging with breakfast in Buenos Aires.<br>
* 3 nights lodging with breakfast in Iguazú.<br>
* 3 nights lodging with breakfast in Ushuaia.<br>
* 3 nights lodging with breakfast in El Calafate<br>
* Excursions in Buenos Aires: A tour or Buenos Aires City. Dinner &amp;Tango Show. Two golf days.<br>
* Excursions in Iguazú: Excursion to Iguazú Falls on the Argentinean side and Brazilian side.<br>
* Excursions in Ushuaia: Excursion to Fagnano Lake off road 4X4 with lunch box. Golf Day.<br>
* Excursions in El Calafate: Excursion to Perito Moreno Glacier passages.<br>
Not Included:<br>
- Domestic or International flights<br>
- Entrances to National Parks</span></strong></h1>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;"> </span></strong></h1>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;"> </span></strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Day 1: Europe/America</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">With the South Cross Constellation as a guide you fly over the Atlantic Ocean to have an unforgettable experience in Argentina with its incredible scenery and wild nature. Enjoy your quiet flight over the ocean to take a rest, and to prepare for what comes next.</span></strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Day 2: Marvellous Buenos Aires</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">The city tour lets you discover the great city located on the De La Plata river banks. Buenos Aires captures her visitors at first sight, specially its numerous cultural options. “La Reina del Plata”, as it was referred to in tangos, casts a spell on her guests. Theaters, restaurants, cinemas, bars and coffee shopsallow you to discover Buenos Aires’s identity.</span></strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Day 3: Buenos Aires - Golf day</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">After breakfast, you will enjoy a beautiful day of golf. Transfer to Hotel. Lodging.</span></strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Day 4: Buenos Aires / Iguazu</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">In Iguazú, nature offers you an unforgettable sight. 900 meters of passages over Rio Iguazú, and the breathtaking Iguazú falls will astonish you.</span></strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Day 5: Iguazú / “Garganta del Diablo” or Throat of the Devil</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">On the “Jungle Train” you begin the ride to the heart of the Iguazú falls. A walk through the passages will allow you to walk among the waterfalls till you reach the “Garganta del Diablo”. The possibility of having a baptism by these spraying waters, on a short trip by boat, is an optional excursion that is very difficult to resist!</span></strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Day 6: Brazilian falls</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Enjoy the Iguazú falls from the Brazilian sidethrough 900 meters of passages.</span></strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Day 7: Iguazú / Ushuaia</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">A very short flight from Iguazú to Buenos Aires allows you to reach the southernmost place in the world: Ushuaia, a treat to enjoy throughout the year.</span></strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Day 8: Ushuaia, Fagnano Lake off road</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">The excursion to Fagnano Lake on special 4X4 off road trucks, from Ushuaia city traveling across the Southern Andes, to Garibaldi lake to taste some delicious grilled meat.</span></strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Day 9: Ushuaia – Golf day</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">After breakfast, you will enjoy a beautiful day of golf. Transfer to Hotel. Lodging.</span></strong></h1>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;"> </span></strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Day 10: Ushuaia – El Calafate</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">The Glacier air strokes your face softly as soon as you get off the plane coming from Ushuaia. You arrive in “El Calafate” city, the access to the Perito Moreno Glacier.</span></strong></h1>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;"> </span></strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Day 11: El Calafate – Perito Moreno Glacier</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">You reach the glacier by walking along the bridges that let you contemplate the magnificent view of the glacier; it is a soundless white river, with blue tones that wait patiently to fall into the Argentino Lake.</span></strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Day 12: El Calafate - Free day</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"> </h1>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">This region offers lots of options to enjoy The Glaciers´ National Park.</span></strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Day 13: El Calafate – Buenos Aires</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">The plane brings you back to Buenos Aires. Our package includes a Dinner &amp; Tango Show at Esquina Carlos Gardel to discover the secrets of the most famous Argentine dance.</span></strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Day 14: Buenos Aires, Golf day</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">After breakfast, you will enjoy a beautiful day of golf. Transfer to Hotel. Lodging.</span></strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Day 15: Buenos Aires, last day</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">In your trip you have visited the most amazing regions of this planet. Ezeiza airport is your last stop before boarding your international flight.</span></strong></h1>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"> </h1>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"> </h1>
